    <body>
      <section eId="sec_875_E">
        <num>875-E</num>
        <heading>Employee training</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_875_E__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Federal and state laws governing firearm, rifle, and shotgun\ntransfers.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_875_E__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>How to recognize, identify, respond, and report straw purchases,\nillegal purchases, and fraudulent activity.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_875_E__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>How to recognize, identify, respond, and report an individual who\nintends to use a firearm, rifle, or shotgun for unlawful purposes,\nincluding self-harm.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_875_E__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>How to prevent, respond, and report theft or burglary of firearms,\nrifles, shotguns, and ammunition.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_875_E__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>How to educate customers on rules of gun safety, including but not\nlimited to the safe handling and storage of firearms, rifles, shotguns\nand ammunition.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_875_E__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Such other topics the superintendent deems necessary and\nappropriate.\n  3. No employee or agent of any retail dealer shall participate in the\nsale or disposition of firearms, rifles, or shotguns unless such person\nis at least twenty-one years of age and has first received the training\nrequired by this section. The superintendent shall promulgate\nregulations setting forth minimum requirements for the maintenance of\nrecords of such training.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
